Posts.Content: Jenn8907 wrote: I'm 19. When I started my last menstral cycle a few days ago, I noticed a hard lump in my left breast. It doesn't hurt, and it's deep inside, like maybe an inch or less above my rib cage. It's in the lower left corner of my breast. I'm a little concerned because I've been reading about breast cancer tumor characteristics, and it has a few of those. It's not exactly round, and it feels like it has some grooves in it. It does move around a little, though. Does this sound like the real deal, or are there other things that can mimic a breast cancer tumor that closely? I know I need to get it checked.
